193
00:11:32.020 --> 00:11:34.960
it's much more likely we're going to find an early cancer.

194
00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:39.020
We've also included other cohorts which are important controls.

195
00:11:39.320 --> 00:11:42.560
6B are people that have come

196
00:11:42.570 --> 00:11:46.500
into the clinic with cancer that have family history

197
00:11:46.540 --> 00:11:47.500
or a mutation.

198
00:11:48.340 --> 00:11:52.260
Cohort 6C are early-stage pancreas cancers across our

199
00:11:52.620 --> 00:11:56.420
65 centers. So if there are clinical trials upon

200
00:11:56.480 --> 00:12:00.360
which we want to test therapeutics for very early-stage pancreas cancer, we

201
00:12:00.440 --> 00:12:04.360
have such a cohort assembled. And then we've also added in a cyst

202
00:12:04.440 --> 00:12:05.000
cohort,

203
00:12:06.180 --> 00:12:09.620
and we see hundreds of thousands of patients with pancreatic cysts in the United

204
00:12:09.700 --> 00:12:13.480
States every year and still don't have optimization of how

205
00:12:13.600 --> 00:12:15.220
we should make decisions for

206
00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:21.140
duration and frequency of screening, along with who should go to the

207
00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:24.700
operating room.Now, as part of this study, we

208
00:12:25.380 --> 00:12:29.260
have standardized collection of data, three-generation family history,

209
00:12:30.020 --> 00:12:33.360
using pedigree templates, standardized germline testing for all

210
00:12:33.400 --> 00:12:37.110
participants. We track modifiable risk

211
00:12:37.180 --> 00:12:41.050
factors, diabetes, obesity, pancreatitis, smoking, alcohol use,

212
00:12:41.100 --> 00:12:44.800
and we're soon adding in a list of medications, standardized

213
00:12:44.860 --> 00:12:48.480
templates for imaging for both MRI and endoscopic

214
00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:52.380
ultrasound, standardized collection of blood, tumor tissue when

215
00:12:52.420 --> 00:12:56.400
available, and also we obtain CA 19-9

216
00:12:56.440 --> 00:12:59.400
and hemoglobin AC, which may be important for model development.

217
00:13:01.080 --> 00:13:04.920
We now have 11,550 patients in. We started as a

218
00:13:04.980 --> 00:13:08.900
single center in May of 2020, and gradually more

219
00:13:08.920 --> 00:13:11.990
sites have come on. I'll show you where the data is.

220
00:13:12.220 --> 00:13:16.110
We made the investment to have Arbor Research be the data coordinating center.

